explanation:
For checking violations of the MISRA rule banning compiler language extensions, the analyser needs the declarations/definitions for each of the following so it can detect any nonstandard constructs or attributes (e.g. __attribute__, asm, typeof, nested functions, zero-length arrays, anonymous structs/unions used as extensions, compiler-specific calling conventions, extension macros, etc.):

- osal_objtype_t: to verify this typedef/enum does not use compiler-specific extensions (underlying type specifiers, attributes, nonstandard enum extensions).
- osal_id_t: to verify the id type definition is a standard typedef (no packed/extended integer attributes or other extensions).
- OS_ArgCallback_t: callback typedef may hide extension usage (varargs, GCC typeof-based function types, calling-convention attributes) so its exact typedef is required.
- OS_object_iter_t: iterator type/struct definition must be inspected for anonymous/unnamed structs/unions, bit-field uses, flexible/zero-length arrays, packed attributes or other extensions.
- OS_creator_filter_t: filter struct definition is used directly in the function (field types, anonymous members, attributes) and must be checked for extensions.
- OS_ObjectIdIteratorInit (prototype/definition): function declaration could include compiler-specific attributes or nonstandard linkage/specifiers; the implementation might use extensions that affect how it is invoked.
- OS_ObjectIdIteratorGetNext (prototype/definition): as above, inspect for attributes or extension use in prototype/definition.
- OS_ObjectIdIteratorProcessEntry (prototype/definition): required to check for nonstandard parameter types, attributes, or calling conventions and whether the passed callback uses extensions.
- OS_ObjectIdIteratorDestroy (prototype/definition): inspect for attributes or transaction semantics implemented with extensions.
- OS_ForEachFilterCreator (prototype/definition): callback function passed into OS_ObjectIdIteratorInit — its signature/definition must be checked for nested functions, nonstandard linkage or attributes.
- OS_ForEachDoCallback (prototype/definition): callback passed to OS_ObjectIdIteratorProcessEntry — must be checked for nonstandard constructs or attributes.
- OS_SUCCESS: macro/enum value definition may use compiler extensions (complex macros, attribute-laden constants) that must be inspected.

Providing these exact typedefs, struct definitions and function prototypes (and, if available, their implementations or header macros used in their declarations) lets the next analyser detect any explicit compiler extensions employed in the symbols that this function uses.
